    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "The National Arts Centre (NAC) in collaboration with Blurring The Boundaries Arts (BTBA), the Research Centre for Music, Sound, and Society in Canada at Carleton University, the Canadian Accessible Musical Instruments Network, and the International Institute for Critical Studies in Improvisation invites you to Empower Arts 2.0, a public disability arts summit taking place during National Accessibility Week.\n\nWith the generous support of the National Arts Centre and Long & McQuade Musical Instruments.\n\nThis year’s theme, Beyond Access: Reimagining the Stage Through..."
      }
