    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Afro-Andean Funk | Todo Migra Tour |  Fri, Oct 30, 2026, 7:30 pm | Babs Asper Theatre"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/41185/aaf_press_photo_03_photocredit_jc__large.jpg"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "El español sigue al texto en inglés\n\nAraceli Poma grew up in the Andes of Peru, in the house of her grandmother, Mamá Nieves — a community healer whose prayers and songs were the first music she ever knew. She migrated to New York and brought that inheritance with her. \n\nTodo Migra — everything migrates — is a concert that moves the way memory moves: between the Andes and the African diaspora, between Quechua and English and Spanish, between the ritual and the dancefloor. Led..."
      }
    ],
